The country has also recorded 102 new COVID-19 related fatalities on Tuesday. This brings the total number of deaths to 55 976. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in Gauteng. “Regrettably, we report 102 more COVID-19 related deaths: Eastern Cape 3, Free State 32, Gauteng 36, Kwa-Zulu Natal 11, Limpopo 0, Mpumalanga 0, North West 0, Northern Cape 19 and Western Cape 1,” says Dr Mkhize. Recoveries stand at 1 543 951. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 11 406 308. pic.twitter.com/iLCYuy8JVB — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) May 25, 2021 